{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17606031","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17606031"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:08:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:08:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15891"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15891","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15891"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8582"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72854"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8582","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8582"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15891"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58324"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3618"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20571"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20577"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72854","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72854"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring pregnancy, steroid hormone synthesis requires cooperation between the fetus, placenta, and parent since each lacks the complete enzymatic machinery to independently synthesize all required hormones.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following correctly matches the source with its contribution to steroid hormone synthesis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Parent \u2192 LDL cholesterol; Placenta \u2192 3-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase and aromatase; Fetus \u2192 16-alpha-hydroxylase","Parent \u2192 3-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase and aromatase; Placenta \u2192 LDL cholesterol; Fetus \u2192 16-alpha-hydroxylase","Parent \u2192 3-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase and aromatase; Placenta \u2192 16-alpha-hydroxylase; Fetus \u2192 LDL cholesterol","Parent \u2192 LDL cholesterol; Placenta \u2192 16-alpha-hydroxylase; Fetus \u2192 3-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase and aromatase","Parent \u2192 16-alpha-hydroxylase; Placenta \u2192 LDL cholesterol; Fetus \u2192 3-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase and aromatase"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring pregnancy, steroid hormone synthesis requires cooperation between three compartments. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eparent provides LDL cholesterol\u003C/strong\u003E as the basic steroid precursor. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eplacenta contains 3-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase and aromatase\u003C/strong\u003E enzymes necessary for converting precursors into active hormones. The \u003Cstrong\u003Efetus contributes 16-alpha-hydroxylase\u003C/strong\u003E (also called desmolase) through its adrenal glands. The other suggested combinations are incorrect as they misattribute the enzymatic contributions between compartments.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The parent provides low-density lipoprotein (LDL) cholesterol as the basic steroid precursor during pregnancy","The placenta contains aromatase and 3-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase enzymes for steroid hormone synthesis","The fetal adrenal glands contain 16-alpha-hydroxylase (desmolase) for steroid hormone synthesis"],"references":["Chatuphonprasert W, Jarukamjorn K, Ellinger I. Physiology and Pathophysiology of Steroid Biosynthesis, Transport and Metabolism in the Human Placenta. Front Pharmacol. 2018;9:1027. Published 2018 Sep 12. doi:10.3389/fphar.2018.01027","Newbern D, Freemark M. Placental hormones and the control of maternal metabolism and fetal growth. Curr Opin Endocrinol Diabetes Obes. 2011 Dec;18(6):409-16. doi: 10.1097/MED.0b013e32834c800d. PMID: 21986512.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58324"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15891"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58324","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58324"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-22T10:12:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-22T10:13:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8582"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72854"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"3618","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com